    	<h2>Deviation from normal levels indicates the following:</h2>
        <ul>
        	<li>Abnormal levels of haemoglobin, haematocrit or RBCs can be signs of anaemia, heart disease, or iron deficiency.</li>
        	<li>Low white blood cell count might be caused due to a bone marrow disorder, autoimmune disorder, or cancer.</li>
        	<li>High white blood cell count may be because of an inflammation, infection, or a reaction to a medication.</li>
        </ul>
